ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING # Eligibility : 50% of the seats are reserved for candidates who pass their qualifying examination as regular students of schools located in Chandigarh and recognized by the Chandigarh Administration # Duration : 4 years # Study mode : Full time # Approved intake : 75 # Course level : UG # Course Fee : 5.95 lakhs # Approval : University Grants Commission # Details : Electrical Engineers are working today in all areas of our modern information society. Buzzwords such as the internet and the cellular phone$ communication and navigation satellites$ high performance computers$ power plants and high voltage networks$ renewable energy and robotics - in all these fields research$ development and production innovation was strongly influenced by electrical engineers in responsible positions. Employment perspectives are excellent as not only in INDIA $ but also in Western Europe and the United States of America$ where there is a shortage of qualified electrical engineers. From the production of power in power plants and the distribution in high power networks to the customer with his PC in his house hold or office$ it is electrical engineering that influences our daily life in mostly pleasant ways. Electrical engineering thus is a very broad field$ ranging from all aspects of information processing$ power production and power distribution. The main areas are Electrical Machines$ Electrical Power Generation$ transmission and distribution$ Electronics (including micro$ opt and power electronics)$ communication technology$ Microprocessors $ Power systems$ Real Time Systems$ Neural Networks and Fuzzy systems etc. The curriculum of Dept. Of Electrical Engineering$ PEC$ is gingerly designed to provide engineering graduates$ consummate knowledge and skills required for a successful career in the field of Electrical Engineering. The course is at par with changing technology and enables the students to easily manage to multifarious environmental teams.The courses for the undergraduate program in Electrical Engineering is divided in eight semesters with 5-6 courses in each semester. The courses range from Electrical Power to Computer Aided Power System Analysis and Design$ Analog Electronics to Computer Architecture$ Digital Systems and Microprocessors$ Programming Design Methodologies and Data Structures to Real Time Systems$ Control Systems to Neural Networks and Fuzzy Logic Systems etc. Along with technical courses$ Management Principles and Cooperate Laws are also taught to students to acquaint them to the industrial principles. Eligibility Criteria : The admission to the B.E. Courses will be based on the merit of JEE (Main).The candidates desirous of taking admission in any of the above six Institutes will have to register separately with JAC-2013 (Joint Admission Committee).The details of registration and the admission brochure will be available on the Institute/JAC website in the month of May $ 2013. TECH BIOTECHNOLOGY ENGINEERING # Eligibility : All the candidates having rank in AIEEE and must pass 10+2 Examination or equivalent$ with pass marks in Physics$ Chemistry$ Mathematics and English separately. The age Criterion will be as per the directive issued by MHRD from time to time. # Duration : 4 years # Study mode : Full time # Approved intake : 60 # Course level : UG # Course Fee : 2.8 lakhs # Approval : University Grants Commission # Details : B. Tech course in Biotechnology has been started from 2005 with intake of 60 students. The department strives to emerge as a leader in providing excellent education in Biotechnology and to develop cutting-edge technology through research$ training and technical innovation. The department has highly qualified$ experienced and dedicated faculty to provide both classroom teaching and practical instructions. The department actively engages in relevant$ contemporary and state-of-the-art research with several scholars enrolled for the Ph.D. program. Research is going on in the department in different areas of Biotechnology including Environmental Biotechnology$ Microbial Biotechnology$ Molecular Biotechnology$ Food Biotechnology etc. Since commencement$ the department has performed consistently well both in academics and extra-curricula. While two of the students have been nominated for the prestigious KVPV fellowship by the Govt. of India$ several have gone out in the professional world already and presented their research in technical symposia around the country. A number of our students are members of various organizations both in and beyond their core-biotechnology fields$ namely the Literary Circle$ the drama Society$ the Centre for Cognitive Activities and Linux Users Group. >< Course Name : B. The department was built up by a team of dedicated faculty members wit the help of a host of visiting professors deputed by UNESCO to NIT Durgapur. Some of the faculty members were trained abroad under UNESCO programme$ and a number of equipment and instruments were donated by UNESCO to the department.
